INSERT INTO `afrecommendation` (`id`, `form_001_id`, `auditfinding_no`, `subof_no`, `author_id`, `afrecommend`, `management_action`, `approval_status`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fauthor_id`, `first_fu`, `ffu_mgmtaction`, `ffu_status`, `ffu_updated_at`, `ffumgmt_updated_at`, `sauthor_id`, `second_fu`, `sfu_mgmtaction`, `sfu_status`, `sfu_updated_at`, `sfumgmt_updated_at`, `tauthor_id`, `third_fu`, `tfu_mgmtaction`, `tfu_status`, `tfu_updated_at`, `tfumgmt_updated_at`, `final_remarks`, `final_remarks_updated_at`, `final_status`) VALUES
(1, '1', '43', '1', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Before the conduct of physical count, separate PPE from Semi-Expendable items; then, assign property tags and stickers only to PPEs and report to the RPCPPE while the semi-expendables are reflected in RPCSI; Comply with the RPCPPE format provided in Appendix 73 of GAM Volume;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', ' ', '', ' ', '2019-08-14 16:49:04', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(2, '1', '44', '2', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">For the funding requirement, develop a reliable estimate of expenses to be incurred in the conduct of physical count and include it in the project&rsquo;s LIB; or&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Organize a meeting with the Regional Directors, in coordination with the OUSec for ROs and discuss on the possible transfer of the PPEs.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-14 16:51:06', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(3, '1', '45', '3', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Management should require its authorized officials to upgrade the insurance coverage in order to protect the interest of the government against loss or damage caused by insurable risks and other perils such as earthquakes.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Instead of trading the insurance coverage for floods to typhoons, propose to include in annual budget the amount necessary to cover the increase in premium relative to the insurance upgrade.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-14 16:52:26', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(4, '1', '48', '5', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Capacitate the Finance and Administrative Personnel through sending them to trainings to be updated on the laws, rules and regulations from various oversight bodies. Aside from trainings and orientation on RA 9184 and its IRR and other related rules on property and procurement, they should also be sent to trainings on Government Accounting Manual, Laws and Rules on Government Expenditures (LARGE), Cash Management and Control Systems (CMCS) and other related trainings and capability building activities.</p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-14 16:53:57', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(7, '1', '49', '8', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The Cash Unit should ensure that all collections are supported by Order of Payment, regardless of the nature of collection. The OP should be pre-numbered, monitored and originated from the Accounting Unit.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-14 17:07:31', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(8, '1', '50', '9', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Comply with the number of RCDs required by GAM. Ensure that Budget Unit is also informed on the collections of the Institute because these are necessary in estimating revenues and serves as the Unit&rsquo;s input in the preparation of RROR.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-14 17:11:19', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(12, '1', '47', '7', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Assign 2 regular staff, 1 from each Unit, who will be responsible in reviewing, adjusting and recording for reconciling items. Schedule a regular reconciliation (e.g., once a week). Document the agreements and identified items for reconciliation and before the start of the succeeding meetings, check the actions taken.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:08:28', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(15, '1', '49', '8', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Capacitate all the Finance and Administrative Personnel by sending them to trainings and seminars for them to be knowledgeable and updated on the relevant laws, rules and regulations issued by various oversight bodies such as the Commission on Audit (COA), Department of Budget and Management (DBM), Civil Service Commission (CSC), Bureau of Treasury (BTr), Department of Science and Technology (DOST) and other offices. Also, coordinate with the DOST-CO Financial and Management Service to include Cash/Treasury Unit\'s Personnel in their Annual Consultative Assembly of Administrative and Finance Officers (ADAFO) for them to share issues and concerns encountered in their Units.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:09:35', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(16, '1', '43', '1', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Develop physical count guidelines to include creation of Inventory Committee with clear functions and responsibilities, processes, procedures and frequency/schedule of conducting physical count, and the preparation and submission of reports such as RPCPPE, RPCI and the book of accounts;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:11:53', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(17, '1', '43', '1', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Capacitate the Property and Procurement Officers by sending them to training on GAM, particularly on the forms and formats required in report preparation;</span></p>\r\n<div id=\"recommendation_div18\" class=\"row\" style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">\r\n<h4 style=\"margin-left: 10px;\">&nbsp;</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:12:00', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(18, '1', '43', '1', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">For monitoring purposes, the Property Management System developed by the ITD of the DOST-CO may be used. The said information system can provide a complete and reliable information system of Agency&rsquo;s PPEs, aid Property Officers in managing PPE records, make available to the general users their respective accountabilities, generate required reports as needed; and provide security and backup storage of PPE records.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:12:07', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(22, '1', '9', '13', '5', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Look into the hiring mechanism in terms of efficiency and effectiveness and recommend measures to ensure the filling-up of plantilla regular positions before resorting to hiring non-permanent personnel. Consider coming-up with a policy to prioritize&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; existing qualified non-permanent personnel in filling up vacant plantilla positions in consideration of the DBM-CSC JC No. 1, s. 2017.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:33:06', '2020-01-06 15:47:03', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(23, '1', '9', '13', '5', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Come-up with a hiring plan for the immediate processing of the unfilled positions according to urgency and completeness of requirements. </span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:33:42', '2020-01-06 15:47:03', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(24, '1', '9', '14', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Process the immediate update and revision current employee manual and related forms used in the HR to include the EEOP statement in compliance with Sec 83 of the CSC 2017 Omnibus Rules on Appointments and Other Human Resources Actions (Revised 2018).</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:37:37', '2020-01-07 08:35:45', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(25, '1', '9', '15', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Organize a training workshop on coaching mentoring to be able to get an in-depth understanding on how it is done and its benefits to the organization. Initially, involve the participation of personnel who are acting as high as Section Chiefs who will then cascade to their staff. Document the coaching and mentoring sessions through the forms recommended by CSC</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:38:50', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(26, '1', '11', '16', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">An HRD Plan should present how Learning and Development (L&amp;D) interventions will support the achievement of the organization&rsquo;s strategic goals and objectives.&nbsp; It must be continually reviewed and updated to level with the agency needs and priorities. From the list of trainings enumerated in the HRD Plan of the Institute, monitor the trainings attended by each personnel in order to track that all employees have the opportunity to participate at least one training/seminar per year as required by CSC.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:39:59', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(27, '1', '11', '16', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Develop a comprehensive HRD Plan based on the periodic assessment of the needs of the staff. The Plan will address the gaps and propose interventions and will also reflect the acquired skills, abilities and knowledge of an individual employee. It is also necessary to include the action plans to ensure that the learning or competency gained by the staff will be applied in their respective workplace. This will also help the management in creating a sustainable organization.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:40:20', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(28, '1', '9', '15', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Aligned with the implementation of coaching and mentoring sessions, integrate the seven (7) leadership competencies aspired by CSC:</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Thinking Strategically</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Leading Change</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Building Commitment</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Developing People</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Managing Performance</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Coaching for Results</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Partnering and networking</span></li>\r\n</ol>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:41:12', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(29, '1', '13', '17', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Create a Change Management Team that will assess current workforce of the Institute. Also, the findings and recommendations from the CMT will serve as a basis for requesting of additional permanent personnel.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:51:18', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(30, '1', '13', '17', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">At the same time, if the Institute, upon the recommendation of CMT, assessed that reassigned positions are most appropriately assigned to their current offices, request revision/change in the Rat Plan/PSIPOP to either reflect the current staffing structure or come-up with the most appropriate structure that will be effective in the long run for the Institute. Review status of reassigned personnel, defining criteria for the return or stay of these personnel e.g. urgent need by the original office, willingness of incumbent/ supervisors, expertise and trainings of incumbents, etc., create a transition plan for returning personnel.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:51:33', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(31, '1', '13', '17', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The duties and responsibilities of personnel are attached to the position wherein they have taken their oath.&nbsp; Hence, the functions that must be performed by the reassigned personnel, especially when they are not consistent with those stated in their respective PDFs, must be specified in the Special/Office Order issued to them. Prepare and issue Special Order with specific terms and duties/ responsibilities for all reassigned personnel.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:51:56', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(32, '1', '17', '18', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Aside from the loyalty cash awards of P5,000 or P10,000, depending on the year of service, provide as well non-monetary payments such as memorabilla items or souvenirs, as their remembrance they the awardees reached another milestone of their government service.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:55:51', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(35, '1', '1', '20', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Review the list of position titles prescribed for DOST-GIA personnel. Reclassify their current positions to positions that are best aligned with their to their functions, expertise and areas of assignment.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 09:16:00', '2020-01-07 08:35:45', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(36, '1', '19', '21', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The Collection and Disbursement Unit should strictly comply with the procedures illustrated in GAM and start the practice providing copies of RCD to Budget Unit as basis for recording in the RROR.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 09:25:23', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(37, '1', '19', '21', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The Budget Unit, at the same time, should fully implement the areas of responsibility provided in GAM particularly on maintaining RROR. Although the Unit is not responsible in preparing the Financial Accountability Report No. 5 or the Quarterly Report of Revenue and Other Receipts, RROR will serve as helpful basis in providing estimated/budgeted revenues as well as internal control in checking the amount of revenues recorded and reported by the Accounting Unit.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 09:25:41', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(38, '1', '19', '21', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">udget, Collection and Disbursement and Accounting Sections should strictly comply with the responsibility areas presented in GAM especially in the preparation of reports and registries (RROR and RAOD). The RAOD will serve as check and balance with the records maintained by the Accounting Unit and will be helpful to fast track the reconciliation in case there are variances on the records.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 09:26:01', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(39, '1', '6', '22', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Ensure full compliance to COA Circular 2016-005 by conducting regular and periodic verifications, analysis, and validation of the existence of the receivables. Otherwise, those that are overdue (e.g., more than 10 years) may be requested for write-off.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 09:38:16', '2020-01-07 08:35:45', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(40, '1', '6', '22', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Continue the collection efforts and strategies started in order to increase collection rates and ensure that the payment for the services offered by the government will accrue to the public.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span></span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 09:38:33', '2020-01-07 08:35:45', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(41, '1', '10', '23', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Ensure compliance with the DOST-ITDI Administrative Order No. 002, particularly on its provision relating to the payment scheme. Grace period may also be provided, as long as it will not exceed fifteen (15) days as required. At the same time, follow the credit limit scheme provided by the Administrative Order.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 10:03:18', '2020-01-07 08:35:45', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(42, '1', '10', '23', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Strengthen the collection mechanism through issuance of demand letters and assigning of personnel who will be in-charge of collecting the receivables. Ensure that demand letters are received by the concerned individuals/companies.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 10:03:33', '2020-01-07 08:35:45', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(43, '1', '10', '24', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Coordinate with LANDBANK and Bureau of Customs on the details of these reconciling accounts as a support in preparing the adjusting entries. Reconciling items discovered during the preparation of bank reconciliation statements should be adjusted in the succeeding months.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 10:08:27', '2020-01-06 15:47:03', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(44, '1', '7', '25', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Strictly comply with the COA Circular and GAM and effect the immediate liquidation of cash advances before granting new cash advance.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 10:11:06', '2020-01-07 08:35:45', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(45, '1', '7', '25', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Create a Cash Monitoring Tracker to include the dates of grant and liquidation of cash advances. This will serve as a tracker on the issuance of written reminders and will lessen delays on the liquidation. At the same time, it will be able to monitor the unliquidated balances of SDOs cash advances which will prevent the granting of additional cash advances. For reporting purposes, this will be helpful in the preparation of Report on Aging of Cash Advances.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 10:11:23', '2020-01-07 08:35:45', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(46, '1', '7', '26', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Instead of paying the last payroll cutoff through cash, consider to establish a more concrete cutoff. For example, require employees to submit their daily time records (DTR&rsquo;s) every 10<sup>th</sup> and 25<sup>th</sup> of the month. This will be processed and salaries will be given in the 12<sup>th</sup> or 27<sup>th</sup>, the next banking day if it falls on a weekend or holiday. During the end of the year, for example, last working day is 29<sup>th</sup>, salaries from the second cutoff (day 15-27) will be directly credited to their bank accounts while the last two (2) days, 28<sup>th</sup> and 29<sup>th</sup>, may be paid through cash, so that actual attendance, as required by COA, is still ensured. This will be less risky on the part of the Disbursing Officer and the Human Resource and Management Officer.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 10:12:32', '2020-01-06 15:42:53', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(47, '1', '2', '27', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">In order to ensure and maintain the confidentiality of information stored in these documents, these should be placed along the HR premises. Since the Human Resource Management Section are the primary users of SALN and 201 files, these should be maintained and kept and stored in their areas. Also, to be able to create back-up files in case of lost or damage and for an easier access, especially those old files that are still being requested by former and current employees, start the practice of scanning documents before filing it in data folders.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 10:13:50', '2020-01-07 08:35:45', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(48, '2', '1', '28', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Coordinate with both LBP and DBP and explain the law&rsquo;s requirement that it should be maintained and deposited with DBP. Considering that DBP has already changed its management since the IGF transfer in 2010, schedule a meeting with them, discuss the intention of the law and propose for the possibility of reverting it to them.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:07:34', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(49, '2', '2', '29', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Since provisions on the Trust Agreement was not mentioned in the RA, transfer the Fund to less risky type of deposit such as Regular Deposit. In this case, monitoring will be easier because all deposits and disbursements go in a single bank account. Also, bank reconciliation will be easier as detailed bank statements will be provided by the bank. Moreover, reiterating that the purpose of the Fund is to assist inventors and not for interest income-generation.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:08:57', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(50, '2', '2', '29', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Moreover, propose amendments to RA 7459 to include a provision allowing the Agency to enter into Trust Agreement. Accounting for the amount of interest income accumulated through the years, entering into Trust Agreement resulted in much larger income as compared to Regular Deposit. These income increases the Fund balance which will create better opportunities for inventors to borrow.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:09:16', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(51, '2', '3', '30', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Strict compliance with the DBM-DOF-COA Joint Administrative Order No. 2012-01 on its requirement of submitting complete list of existing bank accounts following the prescribed format.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:11:11', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(52, '2', '3', '30', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Determine the legal basis and purpose of creating the said bank account and send a request to the Permanent Committee, chaired by DOF with DBM and COA, to maintain the said accounts. Otherwise, coordinate with BTr for the immediate closure of the dormant and unauthorized bank accounts.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:11:39', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(53, '2', '4', '31', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Devise marketing strategies such s promotional campaign and advertisements to inform the public and the inventors on this program offered by the Institute.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:13:06', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(54, '2', '4', '31', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Capacitate the Technology Information and Promotion Division (TIPD) as the one responsible for elevating the level of awareness and the promotion of the innovation system strategies. </span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:13:26', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(55, '2', '5', '32', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Establish a mechanism to fast track the collection of loans receivable. Aside from the foreclosure of collaterals, demand letters should also be sent to all delinquent borrowers to serve as a reminder that a certain amount is already due and they are expected to settle. Compute the interest income and penalties accrued from 2014 to present and record the same to the accounting books.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:36:06', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(56, '2', '5', '32', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Also, create a monitoring system that will show the movement of the account, interest and penalties accrued during the period, aging schedule and an updated loan balances that will aid in the preparation of financial statements.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:36:28', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(57, '2', '5', '32', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Update the Agency&rsquo;s existing records on principal, interest and penalties. Check the last interest payments made by the inventors and verify whether provisions on Prescription of Actions provided in Articles 1142, 1144 and 1151, Chapter 3 of the Civil Code are already applicable.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:36:56', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(58, '2', '6', '33', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Upon receipt of the Quarterly Statement of Financial Position and Income Statement, recheck and re-compute whether amounts shown in the report tally with the accounting records. Although Bank Reconciliation is not required because of the absence of bank Statements, prepare your own account reconciliation to check balances, effect adjustments if necessary and inquire reconciling items. Also, verify the Retained Earnings account with Land Bank and matched it with the interest income accumulated through the years.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 16:09:34', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(59, '2', '6', '33', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Maintain a complete and separate filing of all documents such as Statement of Financial Position, Income Statement, Loan approval in case of new grants, disbursements related charged to the IGF and other internal communications from the Agency.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 16:09:51', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(60, '2', '7', '34', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The Quarterly Statement of Financial Position and Income Statement shall serve as the TAPI&rsquo;s records on the movement of the Trust Account. For reconciliation purposes, TAPI should verify and account for all transactions recorded by the bank. In case there are noted variances, these should be investigated, discussed with the LBP representative and adjust when necessary.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 16:37:16', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(61, '2', '7', '34', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Although there are no bank statements, regularly (quarterly) conduct reconciliation of balances to check whether all transactions charged to the funds were captured and recorded.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 16:37:30', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(62, '2', '8', '35', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">To ensure a reliable financial statements reporting, ensure that interest income is recorded on time. Remind the Land Bank of the Philippines with its responsibility to submit the quarterly financial reports within the first twenty (20) banking days following the reference calendar quarter. If accounting books are not yet closed when financial reports are received, booked the interest income at the time the interest was received for a more accurate Investment and Interest Income balance.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 09:08:33', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(63, '2', '9', '36', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Regularly reconcile the interest income recorded in the Quarterly Income Statement against the amounts recorded in the Accounting Books. Adjust the noted variances as necessary. Also, to ensure a matching of revenue of expenses and a more reliable account balances, recognize revenues at the time these are earned and not when the Quarterly Financial Reports are delivered and received by the Institute.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 09:32:01', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(64, '2', '10', '37', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">In compliance with the Account Codes and Titles specified in GAM Volume III, use the Account Name &ldquo;Other Investment&rdquo; instead of &ldquo;Other Investments and Marketable Securities&rdquo; in preparing the Monthly Trial Balance and Year-end Financial Statements, including the Notes to Financial Statements.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 09:33:34', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(65, '2', '11', '47', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Properly plan the program of activities and budgetary requirements every month. Ensure that all activities are funded and disbursement coincide with the plan. Since NCA releases are based on the MDP, make it as an strategy to program and breakdown the P10,000,000.00 annual IGF appropriation to the end of each quarter, including the last quarter, to save the possible lapsing of unutilized NCA.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 10:57:10', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(66, '2', '11', '47', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Also, ensure that the quarter or month this was shown in the MDP should coincide with the actual month/actual this was deposited to LBP.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 10:57:27', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(67, '2', '12', '48', '5', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">For a more accurate and reliable financial statements and reporting, always check and maintain a reconciled amount of the General ledger and Subsidiary Ledger. When GLs are updated, make sure that SLs are also updated. Also, use the Quarterly Reports issued by LBP as a reference material on the movements of the account and in case there are noted variances, adjust the records as necessary.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 11:14:39', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(68, '2', '12', '48', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Under the GL for Loans Receivable, create SL for each of the borrower. Regularly update the record in case there are collections, additional loan releases, interest income and penalties. This updated record will also help the Institute when there are requests for write-off, restructuring or condonation.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 11:14:57', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(69, '2', '12', '48', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The Notes to FS should discuss clarification on the accounting policies and procedures followed by the Agency and other disclosure requirements such as legal basis and balances.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 11:15:13', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(70, '2', '12', '48', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Regularly reconcile the Investment Account maintained by both LBP and TAPI. Discrepancy on the balances that are unknown to the Institute should be discussed with them.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 11:15:31', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(71, '2', '12', '48', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Also, considering the materiality of its amount, always monitor the movement of the Loans Receivable.&nbsp; Compute, review and record collections, penalties and interest income on time.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 11:15:48', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(72, '2', '5', '32', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Ensure that all transactions related to IGF are recorded under the the IGF Account so that all transactions, collections, deposits and disbursements will be reconciled with the records maintained by the Bank. A separate monitoring tracker for the fund is also recommended to lessen the probability of depositing to an incorrect bank account. This will also help the Division in getting additional work for communication and coordination with concerned oversight agencies to release back the incorrect deposits.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 14:32:37', '2019-09-25 14:34:10', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(73, '2', '13', '50', '5', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Comply with Section 4, Article 2 of RA 7459. Before processing proposals for the increase in the amount of prizes, secure approval from the Institute. Said proposal, approval and LIB should also be attached as additional supporting documents in processing payments and for FAD&rsquo;s information as well.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 16:02:32', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(75, '2', '14', '53', '7', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Ensure that the 12% minimum allotment required by DBM should be utilized for IDAF purposes. Expedite the Institute&rsquo;s activities to assist potential or actual inventors in their initial experiments and prototype development in compliance with the provisions of RA 7459.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 11:15:34', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(76, '1', '8', '54', '38', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Review the current PM for billing and propse revisions to provide more accurate and updated process in the billing of ADMATEL. Also, check the positions of the personnel responsible in each of the processes.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 11:16:01', '2020-01-06 15:42:53', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(77, '2', '14', '53', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Create an internal guideline on the proper utilization of IDAF including the nature of expense that should be charged to the Fund. Coordinate with the Department of Budget and Management (DBM) and request the 12% of the annual MOOE appropriation as a separate Program, Activities and Projects (PAP) to be used solely for IDAF purposes.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 14:09:45', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(78, '2', '15', '55', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Improve the existing marketing strategies/campaigns made in inviting inventors. Keep them informed and updated on the programs and activities offered by the Institute. Encourage them to avail the funds intended for them and for their inventions. Capacitate personnel from TIPD who are responsible for the said activity.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 14:32:29', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(79, '2', '16', '56', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Re-issue a memorandum reiterating the need to properly identify the charging of expenses for it affects the reliability of financial reports and the fund utilization rate. In case funding source was not specified in the ORS, return the said documents to the end-users or requesting office and let them fill-it up of at least specify whether it should be charged under IDAF, IGF or a regular MOOE disbursement.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 14:33:51', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(80, '2', '16', '56', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Furthermore, create specific guidelines on the charging of expenses to IDAF and IGF for a more accurate reports.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 14:33:56', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(81, '2', '16', '56', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Strengthen the internal control system by involve FAD in reviewing and processing of loans. There should be assigned Focal Persons IGF and IDAF Focal Persons in each Division in order to settle issues in recording and monitoring. The identified Focal Persons shall serve as coordinators to ensure that all loan related documents such as request and approval passed through the concerned units.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 14:34:40', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(82, '2', '16', '56', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Also, coordinate with LBP regarding the on-time submission of Quarterly reports to avoid delays in recording and reconciliation.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 14:34:59', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(83, '2', '17', '57', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Ensure that the 12% minimum allotment required by DBM are utilized to assist potential or actual inventors in their initial experiments and prototype development and inventor-development related activities of invention or innovation in compliance with the provisions of RA 7459.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 14:43:33', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(84, '2', '17', '57', '5', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Aside from the Implementing Rules and Regulations (IRR) of RA 7459, create an internal guideline or policy regarding the funding source on where to charge expenses. List down all inventor and invention-related activities of the Institute and define whether related disbursements will be charged to IDAF, IGF, TAPI-GIA, Trust Fund or the Regular MOOE of the Institute.</span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 14:43:52', '2019-08-19 14:48:19', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(88, '1', '10', '60', '3', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Management should establish adequate human resource complement to provide various IT services including but not limited to&nbsp; system analysis and design, programming, system documentation, quality assurance and software testing, system and network administration, and hardware/software support.</span></span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 07:25:04', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' '),
(89, '1', '10', '60', '3', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It should also ensure that there is appropriate segregation of incompatible activities assigned to staff, and prevent one personnel from controlling all key aspects of computer-related operations by proper distribution of tasks among the staff.<br /></span></span></p>', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 07:25:25', '2020-01-06 15:25:16', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ');
