an style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">(10,789,209.39)</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2014</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">To retrieve from COA</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">831,700,138.02</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">n/a</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2015</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">910,313,550.94</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">912,516,42773</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">(2,202,876.79)</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2016</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">962,133,978.88</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">988,912,436.84</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">(26,778,457.96)</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2017</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">1,168,590,144.64</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">1,222,036,966.35</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">(53,446,821.71)</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2018</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">1,417,299,885.45</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">1,688,685,932.95</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">(271,456,047.50)</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-14 17:04:51', '2019-11-05 13:05:08', '0', '2', ' '),
(8, '1', 49, '', '5', 'Administrative Management Division', ' ', 'Compliance to GAM', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><em>Report format of Order of Payment as specified in GAM is not complied with</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Government Accounting Manual Volumes 1 and 2 explained that Order of Payment (OP) should be prepared by the Accounting Section based on a Bill and should be prepared for each payor. Furthermore, Section 40, Chapter 5 of the Government Accounting Manual (GAM) Volume 1 specifies the areas of responsibility and the detailed procedures for collections and deposits made through the Collecting Officer. The Manual stated that the Cash/Treasury Unit Collecting Officer daily receives cash/check from payor representing collection based on the OP prepared by the Accounting Division/Unit. For reference, Appendix 28 of GAM Volume II shows the format and instruction in filling-up the OP form.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the interview with the Financial Management and Administrative Divisions, it was explained that the preparation of OP is assigned to the Accounting Unit. Refunds from cash advances are also supported by OPs. However, services and collections from the OneLab Project are done solely by the personnel assigned in the project through the use of DOST Unified Laboratory Information Management System (ULIMS). The said system can generate an Order of Payment that will be issued to the customers before making payments to the Cashier Unit.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">At the time of audit, the Cashier Unit provided sample OPs and Technical Service Request Forms as attached in <strong>Annexes K1 to K4</strong>. Upon review of the documents submitted, the Auditors noted that the format used is not compliant with Appendix 28 of GAM Volume II as attached in <strong>Annex L</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Also, it was observed that for the services offered by the technical divisions of the Institute, including ADMATEL, are supported by Request for Technical Services. For the Institutes&rsquo; collection from the services of MSD, EBD, CED, PTD, FPD and TSD, request and OP are required by the Cashier unit before processing payments and issuance of official receipts (OR). However, those collections from STD, NMD and ADMATEL were not supported by OPs and considers the request enough in processing payments and issuance of OR.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Since collections from other division did not pass through the Accounting Unit and were not issued with OPs, they were not able to monitor those collections and match with the Report of Collections and Deposits submitted by the Cashier Unit. Aligned with the billing statement or the request for technical services, the OP should serve as the Cashier unit&rsquo;s basis on what is the nature of the collection, how much should be collected and will be helpful in determining the account to where it will be deposited.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-14 17:07:12', '2019-11-26 14:18:23', '0', '1', ' '),
(9, '1', 50, '', '5', 'Administrative Management Division', ' ', 'Compliance to GAM', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><em>Report of Collections and Deposits (RCD) is not submitted to the Budget Unit</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Appendix No. 26 of GAM Volume II (Summary of Forms and Instructions) explains that Collecting Officer/Cashier shall prepare RCD to record the collections and deposits to an Authorized Government Depository Bank (AGDB) as of specific date and shall be maintained by fund cluster. Furthermore, GAM also requires that this report shall be prepared in four (4) copies daily to be distributed as follows:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Original- Cash Treasury Unit/Collecting Officer&rsquo;s file, together with the triplicate copy of the ORs and validated deposit Slips (DSs)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Copy 2- COA Auditor through the Accounting Division/Unit, together with the duplicate copy of the ORs and validated DSs</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Copy 3- Accounting Unit concerned to be attached to the copy of the Journal Entry Voucher (JEV)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Copy 4- Budget Unit</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Based on the Audit Teams interview with the collection Officer, she disclosed that only three (3) copies of the report are prepared and were distributed to the Accounting Unit, COA which is sent through the Accounting unit and the copy of the Cashier Unit. Since then, said reports were not provided to the Budget Unit.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-14 17:11:04', '2019-08-16 14:46:31', '0', '1', ' '),
(12, '1', 5, '', '5', 'Administrative Management Division', ' ', 'Inventory of Bank Accounts', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Non-submission of inventory of bank accounts and non-closure of inactive accounts</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">In order to implement public financial reforms, in compliance with the Administration&rsquo;s thrust to observe transparency and accountability, and to align the direction of the government instrumentalities in collectively pursuing the right path of governance, DBM-DOF-COA Joint Administrative Order No. 2012-01 dated January 6, 2012 requires the submission of a complete list of existing bank accounts showing the following:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Cash Account Title</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Account Name</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Account Number</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Bank/Branch</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Balance per Books</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Month/Year Account was opened</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Purpose of Maintaining the Account</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Legal Basis for Account Creation</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Remarks</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">At the same time, Section 10 of the 2018 General Appropriations Act requires the reversion, closure and transfer the balances of special accounts, fiduciary or trust funds, revolving funds and unauthorized accounts if any of the following instances is met:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">When there is no legal basis for its creation;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">When their terms have expired; or</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">When they are no longer necessary for the attainment of the purposes for which said funds were established.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">In addition, Section 11 of the 2018 GAA prescribes all offices to post on their respective official websites information relating to public funds deposited, maintained and invested by them with any banking or financial institution which shall include, but not limited to the following:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Name of the baking or financial institution/s where public funds are deposited, maintained or invested;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Specific income or fund sources;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Legal basis for depositing, maintaining or investing said income/fund source/s with the bank/s or financial institution/s;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Allowable use/purposes of the income or fund;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Monthly balances of each account of fund; and</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Such other pertinent information as may be reasonably required to be posted by the agency concerned on its website.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Moreover, COA Circular No. 97-001 dated February 5, 1997 was issued to provide Guidelines on the Proper Disposition/Closure of Dormant Funds and/or Accounts of National Government Agencies. Item IV of the same further provides that failure of the officials/employees concerned to comply with the requirements shall be subjected to administrative disciplinary action in accordance with Section 122, Chapter 3, Title III of P.D. 1445 and Section 55, Chapter 10, Sub-Title I-B, Book V of E.O. 292 series of 1987 of the Revised Administrative Code of the Philippines.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Currently, the Institute maintains six (6) Banks Accounts, four (4) of which are MDS Accounts while the remaining two (2) are Current Account. Based on the list of bank accounts submitted during the audit <strong>(Annex M)</strong>, two (2) of the MDS Accounts were already inactive, yet still not requested to be closed. These are the MDS Account Number 2182-9004-20 which is used for the release of fund and payment of accounts payable and the MDS Account Number 2182-9006-67 or the ITDI Special Account</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-14 17:16:58', '2019-11-26 14:19:52', '0', '2', ' ');
