yle=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Technological Services Division</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">48</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">50</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Planning and&nbsp; Management Information Systems Division</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">14</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">16</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Packaging Technology Division</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">17</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">19</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Total</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">247</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">28</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">275</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Upon checking the Personal Services Itemization and Plantilla of Personnel (PSIPOP) submitted by the Human Resource and Management Section as of June 30, 2019, it was noted that out of the 25 vacant positions, sixteen (16) are key positions or those that are SG 18 and above. The details of these unfilled positions, date these were vacated and actions taken by the Institute are shown in <strong>Annex N</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the audit with the personnel from HRMS, it was also disclosed that five (5) of these unfilled positions are still with the Civil Service Commission (CSC) for validation. Once validated, these will be requested by end-users for the posting of Notice of Vacancies&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Moreover, the unfilled position in the Administrative Division are crucial in performing their functions considering that the Top 3 positions (Chief Administrative Officer, Supervising Administrative Officer and Administrative Officer V) were vacated in 2018. Currently, the Administrative Officer V assigned to the Records Section and BAC is acting the OIC of the Division.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">However, per checking of the PSIPOP submitted during the audit, it is noted that some personnel are occupying the same positions and are not promoted for a long period of time. Considering the list of unfilled plantilla positions, they should have been considered as next in rank personnel for those positions.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Table __: ITDI Personnel Occupying the same Postion for a Long Period of Time</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 99px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 33px;\">Name</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 33px;\">Position</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 33px;\">Division</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 33px;\">Date of Lat Promotion</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">Babaylan, Lioba F.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">AO V</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">AD</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">07-19-1994</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 11px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 11px;\">Bustamante, Aida M.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 11px;\">AO IV</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 11px;\">FMD</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 11px;\">09-12-1995</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">Balais, Wilfredo A.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">Senior SRS</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">CED</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">02-01-1994</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 10px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 10px;\">Ugat, Shiela Ruby H.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 10px;\">SR Analyst</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 10px;\">CED</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 10px;\">10-17-1988</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">Esperanza, Ramon C.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">SR Assistant</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">CED</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 15px;\">07-01-1989</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">Unciano, Noel M.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">SRS II</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">EBD</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">10-20-1995</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">Capule, Mario Josefino V.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">SRS II</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">EBD</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">03-16-1994</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">Navarro, Ma. Teresa V.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">Senior SRS</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">MSD</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">01-01-1984</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">Samson, Leonora E.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">SRS II</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">MSD</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">01-01-1984</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:29:08', '2019-11-28 13:08:12', '0', '2', ' '),
(14, '1', 9, '', '5', 'Administrative Management Division', ' ', 'EEOP Principle', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Non-disclosure of Equal Employment Opportunity Principle on MSP and SPMS</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">CSC Resolution Number 1800692 Sec 83 par. 2 states that, &ldquo;<em>There shall be no discrimination in the selection of employees on account of age, sex, sexual orientation, and gender identity, civil status, disability, religion, ethnicity, or political affiliation.&rdquo;</em></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the audit, guidelines in hiring permanent positions are presented. However, upon checking the HR employment manual and form, it is noticed that there is no indication of the Equal Employment Opportunity Principle. Furthermore, it was observed that the guidelines presented is not yet updated version (2016), although they mentioned that it is currently reviewed for revision. At the same time, they have explained that the EEOP is not yet incorporated due to their guidelines are still undertaking revision and this will be considered in the revised version. The Administrative Officer IV stated that the principle already in effect as these are included in the Notice of Vacancies they published and posted, although it is not yet included in their manuals and forms.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:37:12', '2019-08-16 14:48:03', '0', '2', ' '),
(15, '1', 9, '', '5', 'Administrative Management Division', ' ', 'Coaching and Mentoring', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>The Institute has not implemented the Coaching and Mentoring</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The Civil Service Commission (CSC) introduced the Leadership and Coaching Program (LCP) which aims to maximize employees&rsquo; potential through a culture of coaching in the workplace. Coaching is the process that allows an individual to discover their own &ldquo;best benefit&rdquo; and own &ldquo;best self&rdquo;. This helps in assisting the staff/individuals find the solutions themselves to perform better, improve their craft, meet or even yet exceed their targets toward the delivery of efficient and effective public service.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Based on the interview with the Human Resource and Management Section and the other units of both Finance and Administrative Divisions, they have mentioned that there is no formal coaching and mentoring conducted. It was also disclosed that there are times wherein employees in FAD share best practices and ways on how things are done but these are not documented. Sessions for this purpose was not considered by the Human Resource Officer in prior years. </span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:38:21', '2019-08-16 14:48:15', '0', '1', ' '),
(16, '1', 11, '', '5', 'Administrative Management Division', ' ', 'HRD Plan', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>No systematic approach to evaluate the effectiveness of the HRD Plan</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The Omnibus Rules Implementing Book V of Executive Order (EO) No. 292, Rule VIII, Section 7 requires every department or agency to establish a continuing program for the development of personnel and to prepare a comprehensive annual training and development plan.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">CSC Memorandum Cuircular No. 14 s. 2018 Sec 62 states that Continuous learning and development shall be espoused by the Civil Service Commission. Agency heads shall ensure that each employee shall have undergone at least one planned human resource development intervention during the year.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the audit, HRMS provided the Audit Team a copy of their existing HRD Plan. However, it is noted that HRD Plan only includes the seminars and training to be conducted for the year. At the same time, there is no monitoring of the actual seminars/training attended/conducted of the employees. As a result, the agency has no data that would show whether or not all employees have attended at least one seminar every year. The OIC of the HRMS admitted that this particular task was not being monitored because of the limited number of personnel, considering that they handle almost five hundred (500) ITDI employees, both plantilla and contract of service personnel.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">As stated in the EO, the training development plan should be based on the &ldquo;periodic assessment of the needs of the organization and skills/knowledge inventory of the workforce taking into consideration the various levels and categories of jobs in the agency and the urgency of such skills, knowledge and work attitudes required to deliver effective basic services to the public.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The Institute has no structured process of identifying, prioritizing and scheduling the learning and development/training interventions that will address the institutional and performance needs of the agency.&nbsp; </span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 08:39:37', '2019-08-16 14:48:33', '0', '1', ' '),
(17, '1', 13, '', '5', 'Administrative Management Division', ' ', 'Reassignment of Personnel', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Internal movements of personnel by reassignment created inconsistencies with the Rationalization Plan and PSIPOP; Undocumented Reassignment of Personnel</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">CSC Memorandum Circular No. 24, Series of 2017, the &ldquo;2017 Omnibus Rules on Appointments and Other Human Resource Actions defines reassignment as &ldquo;the <em>movement of an employee across the organizational structure within the same department or agency, which does not involve a reduction in rank, status or salary.&rdquo;&nbsp;</em></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Furthermore, Section 13 of CSC MC. No. 24, s. 2017, further states that &ldquo;reassignments will not require the issuance of appointments shall nevertheless require an Office Order issued by the appointing officer/ authority.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the Audit Team&rsquo;s interview and actual audit with the Institute&rsquo;s Human Resource and Management Section, they have revealed that there twenty-one (21) plantilla positions transferred to other division because of the arising need. During the discussion, it was not claimed as reassignment because when these positions are filled-up, qualification standards posted for the positions were based on the requirements set by the new end-user. The HMRS also added that most of these personnel were hired to fit in the functions of the divisions they will be assigned to and not to the functions of the division to which the plantilla item number is supposed to be. However, despite the circumstances and the need, the scenario still falls in the SCS&rsquo;s definition of reassignment. Based on the report provided by the HRMS, the following are the list of reassigned personnel as of June 30, 2019.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Table __: List of Reassigned ITDI Personnel</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">No.</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Name</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Position</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">SG</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; text-align: center;\" colspan=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Division</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">From</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">To</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">1</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Hagad, Victoria T.</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">SRS II</span></td>\r\n<td s