(20, '1', 1, '', '5', 'Administrative Management Division', ' ', 'Duties and Responsibilities of Personnel', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Assigning Technical Positions to Finance and Management Division (FMD)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Currently, the Budget Unit is composed of three (3) plantilla positions and assisted by two (2) contract of service personnel who are acting as Project Accountants. Upon checking the contracts of these two (2) no-regular personnel, it was noted that they are both occupying a Science Research Specialist (SRS) I position which is considered as a technical position. Their salaries were charged to the download Metrology Program entitled &ldquo;Enhancement of the Competence and Capabilities of the National Metrology Laboratory (NML) of the Philippines&rdquo; Project 1. Copies of the contracts are attached in <strong>Annexes P1 to P2</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">As mentioned during the interview, these positions are requested by Budget Unit to the National Metrology Division to assist them in financial related concerns. As specified in their contracts, they are hired to perform the following functions:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Acts as the Project Accountant and will be detailed at FMD;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Controls and monitors the project funds of the download projects;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Prepares the monthly Statement of Allotment, Obligation and Balances;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Prepares the quarterly semi-annual/terminal financial reports;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Prepares other financial reports related to the projects;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Coordinates regularly with the project leader; and</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Does other duties assigned from time to time.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Cases in Point:</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Ms. Angeli Grace C. Gatbonton</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Ms. Rose Therese A. Biglete</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 09:13:45', '2019-11-26 14:24:50', '0', '2', ' '),
(21, '1', 19, '', '5', 'Finance and Management Division', ' ', 'Compliance to GAM', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><em>GAM is not fully implemented due to non-preparation of Registry of Revenue and Other Receipts (RROR) and the disbursement portion of Registry of Allotment, Obligation and Disbursements (RAOD)</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Section 6, Chapter 3 (Budget Execution, Monitoring and Reporting) of GAM Volume 1 requires that the Registries of Revenue and Other Receipts (RROR) shall be maintained by the Budget Division/Unit of NGAs to monitor the revenue and other receipts estimated/budgeted, collected and remitted/deposited.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Furthermore, Section 10 of the same Chapter and Manual provides that the Registries of Allotments, Obligations and Disbursements (RAOD) shall be maintained by the Budget Division/Unit of agencies to record allotments, obligations and disbursement. It shall show the allotments received for the year, obligations incurred against the corresponding allotment and the actual disbursements made.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the Audit Teams interview with the Budget Unit, it was disclosed that they are using an information system called &ldquo;Fox Pro&rdquo; for report preparations and generation, particularly those regularly requested by the oversight bodies such as the Commission on Audit (COA) and the Department of Budget and Management (DBM).Among the reports that can be generated through the system are the Financial Accountability Reports (FARs), Financial Performance Reports (FPR), Statement of Allotment, Obligation and Balances, Financial Report of Operations, various registries and related reports.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">However, instead of preparing for the RAOD as required by GAM, Budget Unit is only preparing and maintaining the Registry of Allotment and Obligation and let the Accounting Unit monitor the Disbursement portion, considering that they are more knowledgeable on the actual disbursements.&nbsp; Because of cutting the process to up to obligations only, it defeats the purpose of the registry which is to prevent incurrence of obligations in excess of allotment and overdraft in disbursements against obligations incurred.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Also, Budget Unit is not maintaining RROR. Currently, the Financial Accountability Report (FAR) No. 5 or the Quarterly Report of Revenues and Other Receipts are prepared based on the RCDs. Since the 4<sup>th</sup> copy of RCDs were not provided to the Budget Unit, they have no reference in recording revenues and other receipts and updating the RROR. They have no basis on how and what amount to input which lead them to not prepare the said registry.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 09:25:05', '2019-08-16 14:51:53', '0', '3', ' '),
(22, '1', 6, '', '5', 'Finance and Management Division', ' ', 'Uncollected Technical Fees', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Material amounts of uncollected technical services fee </strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">COA Circular 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016 prescribes that all government entities shall conduct regular monitoring and analysis of receivables to ensure that these are collected when these become due and demandable.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Per review of the Institutes 2012-2018 Financial Statements, it was observed that there is a material amount of uncollected receivables in years 2012-2018 with a remarkable increased in years 2017 and 2018, as shown in the table below:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Table __: Accounts Receivable Balances</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Year</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>AR Balance (Gross)</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\" colspan=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Changes/Movements</strong></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>All Funds</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><stro