(23, '1', 10, '', '5', 'Finance and Management Division', ' ', 'Compliance to DOST-ITDI AO No. 002', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Failure to comply with the DOST-ITDI Administrative Order No. 002</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">ITDI issued Administrative Order No. 002 <strong>(Annex R)</strong> as a revision for AO No. 001 series of 2015 entitled &ldquo;Prescribing/Guidelines on Rendering the Services Provided by the Advanced Device and Materials Testing Laboratory (ADMATEL)&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Item No. 2 of the said AO specifies that credit limit impose by ADMATEL to their customers. As stated, customers are provided with 3 tier credit limit scheme broken down as follows:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">1<sup>st</sup> Tier- P800,000 for repeating customers (semi-conductor industries) with a good credit standing;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2<sup>nd</sup> Tier- P200,000 for repeating customers (medium enterprises/other industries and academes); and</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">3<sup>rd</sup> Tier- P50,000 for new customers</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">However, based on the 2018 aging of accounts receivables submitted by the Accounting Unit, it was noted that two (2) customers exceeded the P800,000 credit limit.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Cases in point:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">DECA Technologies Inc.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Renato Pleno- CREMA</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Furthermore, Item 3.3 explained that a scheme of 30 days&rsquo; payment term will; be given to the customer upon receiving the Statement of Account and 15 days of grace period if customer exceeds the payment term. The customers from Government agencies are given with a maximum of three (3) months payment term.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Per review of the documents forwarded by the auditee, twenty-four (24) government agencies and forty-three (43) private institutions/individuals have exceeded the maximum of three (3) months and thirty (3) days credit term allowed to them, respectively. As shown in the tables below, these accounts receivables from government agencies and private institutions/individuals amounted to P739,094.00 and P5,247,743.89 as of December 31, 2018, respectively.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Table __: Overdue Accounts Receivable from Government Agencies</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 477px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Government Agencies</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>91-365 days</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Over 1 year</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Over 2 years</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>3 years and above</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Total</strong></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Central Mindanao University</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">94,500.00</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">94,500.00</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%; height: 65px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font