(27, '1', 2, '', '5', 'Administrative Management Division', ' ', 'SALN and 201 Files', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Filing of SALN and 201 Files are done by the Records Unit</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">CSC Memorandum Circular No. 8, series of 2007, discussed the management of 201/120 files. Item No. I specifies that the Head of Office in charge of Human Resource Management, shall be responsible for the establishment, maintenance and disposal of 201/120 file of each personnel in their respective agencies which consist of copies of the following documents:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Appointments</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Assumption to Duty</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Certification of Leave Balances</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Clearance from Property and Money Accountabilities</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Contracts of Services</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Copies of Certificates of Eligibilities</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Copies of Diplomas, Commendations and Awards</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Copies of Disciplinary Actions</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Copy of Marriage Contract</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Designations</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Medical Certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">NBI Clearance</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Notices of Salary Adjustments/Step Increments</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Oaths of Office</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Personal Data Sheet</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Position Description Forms</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Also, the Human Resource Manager shall keep copies of the Statement of Assets, Liabilities and Net Worth (SALN) of retired/separated employees for a period of ten (10) years and their Personal Data Sheet and Clearance from Property and Monetary Accountabilities for five (5) years.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the Audit Team&rsquo;s interview with the Records and Human Resource and Management Sections, they have disclosed that 201 and SALN of employees are currently maintained by the Records Section and stored in their area. This is due to the limited number of personnel assigned to the HRM Section and the unavailability of space or storage area. Since this is for HRMS&rsquo; primary use, they are allowed to access the said documents anytime. </span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 10:13:29', '2019-08-16 14:56:00', '0', '2', ' '),
(28, '2', 1, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Compliance to RA 7459', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Transfer of the Invention Guarantee Fund (IGF) to the LandBank of the Philippines (LBP) is not in accordance with RA 7459</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Article V, Section 9 or the Invention Guarantee Fund (IGF) of RA 7459 states that &ldquo;<em>For an effective implementation of this Act, the IGF created by Republic Act No. 3850, as amended, deposited with the Development Bank of the Philippines (DBP), and the interest earnings thereof, shall be made available to finance and guarantee the loan assistance of any patented Filipino invention duly certified by the Filipino Inventors Society and by the Screening Committee created under Section 4 of this Act.&rdquo;</em></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Since the start of the fund until 2009, IGF was deposited with the Development Bank of the Philippines through an Escrow Agreement. However, this did not prosper which caused DBP to decide returning the outstanding fund balance amounting to P84,635,346.12 to TAPI on January 11, 2010 through DBP Check No. 0030925965. To reduce the risk of handling and safekeeping of the check, TAPI entered into Trust Agreement with LBP on February 8, 2010 through TA No. 05-2019 which is also known as the &ldquo;TAPI INVENTION GUARANTEE FUND&rdquo;. The letter from DBP regarding the transfer of the Fund is attached in Annex A. This action of transferring IGF Fund from DBP to LANDBANK is contrary to the provisions of RA 7459.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:07:18', '2019-08-19 15:07:37', '0', '3', ' '),
(29, '2', 2, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Compliance to RA 7459', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>The Institute&rsquo;s move to enter into a Trust Agreement with the Land Bank of the Philippines (LBP) was not required/prescribed by RA 7459.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Article V, Section 9 of the same Act further states that<em> &ldquo;The interest earnings thereof, shall be made available to finance and guarantee the loan assistance of any patented Filipino invention duly certified by the Filipino Inventors Society and by the Screening Committee created under Section 4 of this Act. Appropriations under this Act and interest earnings of the Fund shall form part of the Fund to pay for the finance and guarantee of loan assistance, cash rewards and other incentives to inventors provided under this Act&rdquo;.</em></span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><em>&nbsp;</em></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">After DBP&rsquo;s transfer of the IGF to TAPI in January 2010, TAPI, entered into a Trust Agreement with the LBP through TA No. 05-209, executed on February 8, 2010 (Annex B).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">As a result, this agreement gave the LBP-Trust Banking group an opportunity to invest and reinvest the undisbursed balance of the Fund in a non-credit risk government security such as Treasury Bills or Notes and Retail Treasury and other instruments guaranteed by the government.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Section 6, Article IV (Liability of the Trustee) of the Trust Agreement further provides that &ldquo;Pursuant to Section 107 and Subsection 409.1 of the manual for Banks and Other Financial Intermediaries (Book 1) as promulgated under Monetary Board Resolution No. 1065 dated 8 October 1990, this Trust Agreement does not guarantee a yield, return or inccome on the investments/reinvestments of the Fund as the same can fall as well as rise depending on prevailing market conditions: losses if any, shall be for the account of TAPI and that this Trust Agreement is not covered by the Philippine Deposit Insurance Corporation (PDIC).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Moreover, entering into Trust Agreement was not specified in the provisions of RA 7459. No authority was granted to TAPI to enter into such an agreement. Since said TA allows LBP to reinvest the said amount, the Fund is prone to higher risks, considering that said activity was not covered by insurance. The purpose of the <strong>Fund</strong> to fund guarantee claims or guarantee premiums on loan/financing exposure of financial institutions, cash rewards and incentives of Filipino inventors and special financing programs for Filipino inventions was defeated when the Institute entered into this Trust Agreement.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">When this was discussed with the personnel from the Finance and Administrative Division, they claimed that interest earned (as evidenced by records) is much higher as compared to a regular deposit. As of December 31, 2018, per bank&rsquo;s report, accumulated income amounted to P39,934,330.30 (Annex C). However, although interest income increases the Fund balance and creates more opportunity for inventors to borrow, the activity became more of an &ldquo;investment for profit&rdquo; rather than serving its purpose. </span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:08:31', '2019-08-19 15:13:29', '0', '1', ' '),
(30, '2', 3, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Legal basis for Bank Accounts', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>No legal basis for maintaining Cash-Local Currency Current Account 1822-1020-81</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">In order to implement public financial reforms, in compliance with the Administration&rsquo;s thrust to observe transparency and accountability, and to align the direction of the government instrumentalities in collectively pursuing the right path of governance, DBM-DOF-COA Joint Administrative Order No. 2012-01 dated January 6, 2012 requires the submission of a complete list of existing bank accounts showing the following:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Cash Account Title</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Account Name</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Account Number</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Bank/Branch</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Balance per Books</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Month/Year Account was opened</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Purpose of Maintaining the Account</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Legal Basis for Account Creation</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Remarks</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Since IGF is deposited through a Trust Agreement, the Agency has no information on the outstanding balance of the IGF until they receive the Quarterly Statement of Financial Position and Income.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">In order to still monitor their disbursement for IGF, except for loans granted, they opened a Cash-Local Currency Current Account 1822-1020-81. Every after two (2) years, they withdraw amounts to be used as prizes for NICE Awardees and to fund the travel assistance given to inventors. The amount withdrawn are redeposited to their Cash-LCCA 1822-1020-81.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">As such, they receive the month bank statements from LBP and prepare a monthly Bank Reconciliation Statement (BRS) for this account. As of 2018, the said account has an outstanding balance of P38,408.24 as shown in Annex D.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">However, when asked on the legal basis for opening the said account, FAD mentioned that it was opened a long time ago and was used for the sole purpose of monitoring the disbursements charged to the fund. They were not able to provide an Inventory of the Bank Accounts they maintained and submit the same to the Bureau of Treasury and to COA.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:10:53', '2019-08-19 15:17:52', '0', '1', ' '),
(31, '2', 4, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Granting of Loans to Inventors/Beneficiaries', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><em>Granting material amounts of loans to limited number of inventors/beneficiaries due because such programs offered by TAPI are not known to inventors</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Section 10, Article V of the same Act or the Financial and Loan Assistance from Government Banks discussed that loan assistance for the commercial production of an invention, either locally or for export and duly certified by the Filipino Inventors Society, and the Screening Committee shall be extended by government banks. Provided, that said invention meets the criteria that would enhance the economy of the country such as profitability and viability, dollar earning capacity, and generation of employment opportunities for Filipinos: Provided, further, that said loan shall be guaranteed by the IGF.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Based on the summary of loan balances as of December 31, 2018 (Annex E) which was provided by the Accounting Unit during the audit, there were thirteen (13) individuals/companies who were able to avail loans offered through the IGF. As of 2018, the total of the principal amount provided to the inventors amounted to P57,120,399.14.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Cases in point:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Arambulo, Rodolfo C.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Baring JV</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Ecarma, virgilio V.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Magdaraog, Adela</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Melano, Arquilo</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Obligar, Rizal A.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Plaza, Felicito P.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Sagana 100 Philippines</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Simon, Juanito A.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Trebel International Inc.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Vazquez Building Systems Inc.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Veraluz International Inc.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Yrezabal and Company</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">As explained during the interview and based on the 2013 report submitted by the Accounting Unit, the latest loan released to an inventor was the P1,252,378.00 granted to Adela Magdaraog on July 19, 2004. TAPI disclosed that they stopped the release of loans to inventors because of the material amounts that are still due for collection. They also claim that inventors are not availing such benefit.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:12:51', '2019-08-19 15:35:29', '0', '1', ' '),
(32, '2', 5, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Overdue Loans Receivables', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Long overdue Loans Receivable which resulted in large amounts of penalties and interest receivables </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Section 7 of the Implementing Rules and Regulations (IRR) of RA 7459 explained the Financial and Loan Assistance from Government Banks that maybe covered by IGF. Section 7.2 specified that the term of loan shall be determined by the cash flow and/or return on investment (ROI) of the project. In no case shall the term exceed five (5) years unless a longer term is justified.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Related to long overdue lonas receivables, the following criteria discussed in Chapter 3 (Prescription of Actions) of the Civil Code further provides that:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Article 1142: A mortgage action prescribes after ten (10) years</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Article 1144: The following actions must be brought within ten (10) years from the time the right of action accrues:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Upon a written contract;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Upon an obligation created by law;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Upon a judgment.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Article 1151: The time for the prescription of actions which have for their object the enforcement of obligations to pay principal with interest or annuity runs from the last payment of the annuity or of the interest.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">However, based on the report submitted by the Agency, it is noted that loans granted to inventors already exceeded the 5-year contract provided in the IRR. As of December 2018, years the loans are outstanding ranges from 16 to 22 years, which is more than triple the number of years allowed by the IRR.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Table __: Aging of Loans Receivable</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Account Name</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Outstanding Principal Amount (based on the documentes provided)</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Date of Loan</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">No. of Years</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Rodolfo C. Arambulo</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">11,040,171.36</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">07-10-1999</span>