azquez Building Systems Inc.</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">8,295,558.29</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">07-09-1998</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">20</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Veraluz International Inc.</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">7,037,944.00</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">02-09-2001</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">17</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Yrezabal and Company</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">5,421,869.73</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">11-27-1996</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">22</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">As shown, all loan balances are long overdue and as a result, interest and penalties accumulated exceeded the principal amount of loan. Based on the summary of loan balances as of December 31, 2013 provided by TAPI, the most recent monitoring they have, accrued interest and penalties ranged from 88% to 405% of the principal and are still uncollected as of the time of audit. The computed Accrued Interest and Penalties of Loans Receivable, including the percentage of these amounts to the principal as of December 31, 2013, TAPI&rsquo;s latest record, is attached in Annex F.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Based on the new information provided by the auditees on August 16, 2019, P1,419,898.91 of the loans receivables was collected from the following individuals in years 2018 and 2019:</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 279px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 44px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 44px;\">Name</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 44px;\">Date of Payment</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 44px;\">Amount</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Felicito P. Plaza</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\">April 2018</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\">117,474.91</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 141px;\" rowspan=\"3\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Yrezabal and Company</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\">July 2018</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\">1,000,000.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\">March 2019</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\">151,212.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\">March 2019</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\">151,212.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Total</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px;\"><strong>1,419,898.91</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">However, these were not reflected in the General Ledger provided to the Audit Team at the time of audit. The same was also not reflected Quarterly Finance Position from LBP. The Personnel from FAD explained that the said amounts were directly directly paid to TAPI and was erroneously deposited to the Bureau of Treasury (BTr) instead of depositing it to the IGF Trust Account. In order to correct it, they already sent a letter to BTr requesting that the P1,149,898.91 be released back to them as this is for IGF purposes. A certificate approving the said request was issued by on July 10, 2019, attached in Annex G. Currently, they are already coordinating with DBM for the release of the Notice of Cash Allocation (NCA).</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-15 15:35:15', '2019-08-19 15:37:49', '0', '1', ' ');
