(33, '2', 6, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Account Reconciliation and filing of Financial Records', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Incomplete Financial Reports; The accumulated balance of interest income reported by LBP is not checked and reconciled by TAPI</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">As specified in Article II, Section 3 (d) of the Trust Agreement (TA No. 05-209) or the Powers and Duties of the Land Bank of the Philippines- Trust Banking Group (LBP-TBG), LBP-TBG shall submit to TAPI the quarterly financial reports, i.e. Balance Sheet, Statement of Income and Expenses, and Summary of Investments, and the Schedule of Guarantee Payment within the first twenty (20) naming days following the reference calendar quarter.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the audit, TAPI provided a copy of the Quarterly Statement of Financial Positions and Income Statements they received from LBP. However, based on the submission and verified from their file, it was noted that three (3) quarterly reports are not filed and missing.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Cases in point:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">March 2013</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">March 2016</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">September 2016</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Moreover, Income Statement showed the interest income earned by the Fund for the period while the Statement of Financial Position shows the Accumulated Interest Earnings, from the time of investment to present, as well as outstanding balance of the Fund. Since no Bank Statements were provided to TAPI, recording of interest was based on the interest income recorded in the Income Statement. Sample of the report is attached in Annex H.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The auditors reconciled the &ldquo;Retained Earnings&rdquo; account presented in the Statement of Financial Position by accumulating the Quarterly Interest Income earned by the Fund. During the reconciliation, it was noted that in years 2014 to present, the amount presented in the &ldquo;Retained Earnings&rdquo; account do not tally with the sum of all interest income earned in prior years. Also, this was not checked by TAPI because there is no reconciliation of the account and recording of interest income are based on these financial reports.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Based on our analysis and computation, the accumulated interest earnings reported in the Statement of Financial Position and the reconstructed amount for Retained Earnings account are as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Table __: Interest Earned by the IGF</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Quarter/Year</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Amount</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Accumulated Retained Earnings</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Variance (for recon)</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Per IAS Computation</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Per LBP</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Retained Earnings, Dec. 2010</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2,812,558.73</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2,812,558.73</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Mar 2011</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">828,597.17</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: