(34, '2', 7, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Account Reconciliation and filing of Financial Records', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Transactions Recorded in Accounting Books are not reconciled with those of LBP</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">In order to establish the reliability of the outstanding balance of the Investment Account, the auditors reconciled balances based on the records provided by the Accounting Unit and the Statement of Financial Position from the Land Bank of the Philippines. Considering that Retained Earnings recorded by LBP is overstated by P799,327.31 as computed in internal audit finding above, the reconstructed retained earnings account, based on the accumulated interest earnings, was used in the reconciliation.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">After the reconciliation made with the Investment account, the following observations were noted:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u>2011</u></strong></span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The beginning balances of the 2011 accounting records showed an understatement of P646,005.81;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Recorded interest income prior to 2011 were overstated by P651,03571;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Collections were overstated byP10,000;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Interest income was overstated by P93,252.17;</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u>2012</u></strong></span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Collections were overstated by P10,000;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Interest Income is understated by P98,282.07;</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u>2013</u></strong></span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Collections were understated by P10,000;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Disbursement were overstated by P10,000;</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u>2014</u></strong></span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Collections were understated by P160,000; and</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u>2016</u></strong></span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Additional Deposit (excess of the cash withdrawn) was overstated by P20,000.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">In addition, it was also observed that in 2018, the balance of investment balance is overstated by P5,000,000. As explained by the Accountant during the interview, it was due to the late recording of the term loan from their I-TECH program which was granted to MYKL Trading, Incorporated. The Accounting Unit was not able to include it in their 2018 transactions because books were already closed when they received the Financial Reports. Per checking, this amount was recorded on March 31, 2019 through JEV No. 2019-03-0255. The effect of these over and under recording resulted in a net underrecording of P4,680,000 as presented in the table below.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Table __: Detailed Reconciliation of the Investment Account</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Particulars</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Per Book</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Based on Corrected Retained Earnings</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Variance</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Amounts</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Beginning Balance, 2011</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">86,014,245.81 </span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">86,660,251.62 </span