(35, '2', 8, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Recording of Interest Receivable', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Late recording of Interest Income for the IGF</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Article II, Section 3 (d) of the Trust Agreement (TA No. 05-209) or the Powers and Duties of the Land Bank of the Philippines- Trust Banking Group (LBP-TBG), LBP-TBG shall submit to TAPI the quarterly financial reports, within the first twenty (20) banking days following the reference calendar quarter.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Per inspection of the documents submitted by LBP, it was observed that said reports show the date and time it was generated. However, the date when it was received by TAPI was not known because reports were not stamped as &ldquo;RECEIVED&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">As explained by the Accountant during the interview, it was mentioned that LBP is always delayed in submitting reports. Since recording of interest income are only based on the quarterly reports, quarterly accounting for this was not done on time and records only at the time the reports are received. As a result, there is a delay in the recording of interest income which creates an understatement of the account during the period covered. Upon checking their General Ledger for Investment Account, most interest income were recorded.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The auditors reviewed and compared the timing of recording of interest income and found out that out of the 32 quarters, that is the 8 years audit coverage (2011-2018), interest for the 8 quarters or 25% were recorded on time, 10 or 31.25% were delayed by 1 month, 4 or 12.5% were delayed by 2 months, 6 or 18.75% were delayed by 3 months or 1 quarter, 1 or 3.125% was delayed for 4 months, 1 or 3.125% for 5 months, 1 or 3.125% for 6 months or 2 quarters and 1 or 3.125% was delayed by 9 months or 3 quarters.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Table __: Comparison on the Timing of Interest Income Recognition</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 1598px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Date of Recognition</span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Reference</span></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Per LBP</span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Per TAPI</span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Reference</span></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Mar 2011</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3333%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helve