(53, '2', 14, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Fund Utilization', '<p><strong>Low utilization rate of the Invention Development Assistance Fund (IDAF)</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Section 7, Article IV or the Invention Development Assistance Fund (IDAF) of RA 7459 provides that IDAF shall amount to at least twelve percent (12%) of the annual operations fund of TAPI and the funds arising from donations, bequests, and other sources, public, private or domestic or foreign. This Fund shall be used in assisting potential or actual inventors in their initial experiments and prototype development and other inventor-development related activities of invention or innovation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Based on the audit team&rsquo;s interview with the personnel from FAD, they have not received donations during the years covered by the audit. They are utilizing their own budget for these purposes by allocating 12% of the annual operating fund of the Institute, particularly the Maintenance and Other Operating Expense (MOOE) account.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Based on the reports submitted by the Finance and Administrative Division, the 12% budget allocated for the Fund was not fully utilized in years 2011, 2012, 2013, 2015, 2017 and 2018. A remarkable performance was recorded in years 2014 and 2016 when they exceeded the 12% allotment for IDAF and showed an obligation utilization rates of 102% and 192%, respectively.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Table __: IDAF Utilization</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">Year</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">IDAF Budget (12% of GAA-MOOE)</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">Amount Obligated</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">Utilization Rate</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">2011</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">4,146,240.00</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">2,357,494.09</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">56.86%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">2012</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">5,652,240.00</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">4,802,998.67</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">84.98%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">2013</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">4,999,920.00</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">4,731,894.79</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">94.64%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">2014</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">5,416,320.00</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">5,545,573.29</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">102.39%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">2015</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">8,075,760.00</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">6,505,212.68</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">80.55%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">2016</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">8,184,312.00</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">15,699,146.20</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">191.82%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">2017</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">8,178,312.00</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">5,213,699.21</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">63.75%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">2018</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">8,671,152.00</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">6,043,848.49</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">69.70%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%;\">Total</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">53,324,256.00</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">50,899,867.42</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">95.45%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-16 17:08:55', '2019-08-16 17:08:55', '0', '3', ' '),
(54, '1', 8, '', '38', 'Finance and Management Division', ' ', 'Billing Procedure Manual', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Minor Error in the Billing Procedures Manual</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the audit, the Accounting Unit presented a Procedures Manual on billing with a document code PM-FMD-05-01 effective November 3, 2011 as attached in <strong>Annex W</strong>. Per checking, it was noted that after receiving a conforme letter/Memorandum of Agreement or Technical Servie Request (TSR), the Accounting Unit will prepare a Statement of Account (SOA) and the same will be approved by the Chief administrative Officer (CAO) of the Finance and Management Division (FMD). After approval, they will verify whether the client/customer has an outstanding account or unpaid services in the prior period and if not, they will be releasing the Order of Payment (OP). </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In case the client/customer has an outstanding balance or unpaid account a registered collection or demand letter will be sent. I case the demand letter was returned to sender, they will still released an OP while request for write-off will be made in case demand letter was received by the client/customer. </span>There seems to be a conflicting flow of activities in the process of sending demad letters and the request for write-off.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 11:15:02', '2019-11-26 14:36:40', '0', '1', ' '),
(55, '2', 15, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Fund utilization', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Low utilization rate of the Invention Guarantee Fund (IGF)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">When the Fund was reverted by DBP to TAPI on January 11, 2010, the outstanding fund balance amounted to P84,655,437.85, recorded through JEV No. 010-02-039.At the end of 2010, accounting records showed an updated IGF balance of P86,014,245.81. Movements in the account are caused by the deposit of the additional appropriation, collections from Universal Fabricators, Inc., interest income, adjusting entries to address AOM 2010-001, travelling expenses incurred by inventors (V. Malang and A. Mateo) and other adjustments.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">As shown in their records, the required P10,000,000 annual appropriations for IGF in 2011-2018 was released to the Institute. However, because the granting of loans was stopped, expenses incurred in the years covered by the audit pertains only to the prizes given to NICE Awardees and a travel assistance provided to Mr. Leonardo Mejia Yu in 2013. For the past eight (8) years, 2011-2018, utilization rate of the IGF ranged from 32% to 52%. Aside from the newly granted loan in 2018 through the Institute&rsquo;s I-TECH Program, there were no other disbursements incurred which leads to a low utilization rate of the IGF budget.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Table __: IGF Utilization</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; 