(56, '2', 16, '', '5', 'Finance and Administrative Division (FAD)', ' ', 'Grant and processing of Loans', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Section 5 and 6 of the 2005 Implementing Rules and Regulations of RA No. 7459 otherwise known as the Inventors and Invention Act of the Philippines differentiated the purposes of IDAF and IGF.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Section 5.1.1 of the IRR provided that the IDAF shall be used to assist potential and actual inventors in their initial experiments and proto-type development as well as in other development-related activities for certain invention or innovation. On the other hand, Section 6.1.1 to 1.3 explained that IGF shall be used to guarantee the loan assistance of government banks to patented Filipinos</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the interview with the FAD Personnel, the auditees were informed that the processing and approval of loans as well as other disbursements such as NICE Awards and travel assistance were assigned by the Technical Division such as the Invention Development Division (IDD) and the Investment and Business Operations Division (IBOD). Once supporting documents are completed, these are forwarded to FAD for processing and payment.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">However, the fund on where to charge disbursements is still not clear. To address such, they already issued a memorandum (Annex N) requesting all end-users to identify the expenses that are chargeable to IDAF and input it in the Obligation Request and Status (ORS) and Disbursement Vouchers before forwarding documents to FAD. Despite the reminder, some end-users still leave it blank and let the Budget Unit responsible to determining the proper charging of such expenses.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">As regards the processing of loans, it was explained that this does not pass through FAD and they were only informed when IBOD notifies them or upon receipt of the Quarterly Reports from LBP. On TAPI&rsquo;s part, processing and approval of loans is delegated to IBOD. Once processed and complied with the documents required by the Institute, this is endorsed to LBP for assessment, further processing and approval. LBP notifies the Institute, through IBOD, when the loan request was approved. This notification is forwarded by IBOD to FAD for information and sometimes, when failed to forward, FAD is notified through the Quarterly Reports. As a result, the P5,000,000.00 loan granted and approved in October 2,2018 was only recorded in 1<sup>st</sup> Quarter of 2019.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 14:33:20', '2019-08-19 16:26:54', '0', '3', ' ');
