ght: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">130,292.35</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2014</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">118,176.44</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">2016</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">3,557,934.95</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 47px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Total</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 47px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>3,806,403.74</strong></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-19 14:43:10', '2019-08-19 14:44:14', '0', '3', ' '),
(59, '1', 8, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'IT Governance', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Unrealized importance of the MIS Section in achieving the organization\'s strategic goals</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">IT Governance is defined as the processes that ensure the effective and efficient use of IT in enabling an organization to achieve its goals. It is a framework that provides a way of aligning IT strategy with the business strategy and ensuring that IT generates value in the organization.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The Management Information Systems (MIS) Section is responsible for the development, maintenance of information systems, management of computer network infrastructure, and provision of various IT-related support services.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The MIS Section is part of the Planning and MIS Division (PMISD) under the Deputy of Administrative and Technical Services.&nbsp; As revealed during the Audit Team&rsquo;s interview, there was a perception in the past that MIS Section should prioritize its own division (PMISD) first before other offices in terms of allocating IT resources and support services. Also, it was generally recognized as a unit that only provided internet services to the Institute.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 07:21:43', '2019-12-26 14:14:22', '0', '1', ' '),
(60, '1', 10, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'MIS Section Staffing Pattern', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Lack of IT staff to effectively perform IT functions/services</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">IT governance can be realized with an appropriate organizational structure. The MIS Section is composed of one (1) Supervising SRS, one (1) Senior SRS, and one (1) SRS I. With this limited number of IT staff, there has been some delays in the implementation, maintenance, and documentation of the developed information systems.&nbsp; They perform multiple job roles; hence, there is no appropriate segregation of incompatible activities (e.g. system analysis/design function separate from programming and database administration function separate from application programming). Case in point: Senior SRS performs programming task and also do software testing for the same system.</span> </span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 07:24:05', '2019-12-26 14:30:25', '0', '1', ' '),
(61, '1', 12, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'Information Technology Steering Committee (ITSC)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>There was no avenue for end-users to regularly discuss their concerns with IT Services; hence, there is a need to connect end-users with MIS Section</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">IT governance is evident if there is a platform for end-users and senior leaders to discuss with the IT Unit their needs and feedback on various IT services.&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Because of the limited number of IT staff, the MIS Section is unable to make a regular consultation with other offices regarding IT matters.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The MIS Section only provides IT support services as the need arises.&nbsp; In case an office needs a particular IT service such as a website or information system, it needs to prepare a request letter addressed to the PMISD Chief.&nbsp;</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 07:26:19', '2019-12-26 14:40:39', '0', '1', ' '),
(62, '1', 20, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'Information Systems Strategic Plan (ISSP)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Lack of computer equipment and software to efficiently perform other technology transfer functions</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">It was mentioned during the audit interview that some of the TSD staff have no computers being used.&nbsp; This is also evident in the current ISSP which showed that the Institute has not yet achieved 1:1 employee to computer ratio. Moreover,&nbsp; some of TSD staff are using old computers which are not capable to run product design and video editing software. The software were being used for product design (i.e., SOLIDWORKS) were only a 2015 version since funds were not available to renew licenses.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Furthermore, they expressed the need to have a software for AVPs and technology simulator software which they can use to promote and demonstrate their technologies to their clients more effectively.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 07:34:27', '2019-12-27 14:54:34', '0', '1', ' '),
(63, '1', 14, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'ISSP Process Flow', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Prescribed Process Flow for the Development of ISSP was not followed</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The recommended Process Flow for the development of ISSP includes conduct of ISSP workshop, organization of the ISSP-Technical Working Group (TWG), assessment of organizational strategy, formulation of IS development strategy, conceptualization of ICT projects, identification of resource requirements, and approval of the ISSP by the agency management.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the audit interview, the 2020-2022 ISSP and the previous ISSPs were only developed by the MIS Section based on the IT intervention/support needed by the Institute&rsquo;s strategic thrusts (i.e. R&amp;D, Technical, and Administrative).&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The preparation of ISSP should have been facilitated as agency-wide planning process if there was an organized ISSP-TWG and MIS Section was part of the Institute&rsquo;s strategic planning activities.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">It was revealed that MIS was never involved in any strategic planning activities prior to the development of 2020-2022 ISSP. It was only recently that the MIS participated in the planning workshop of the Institute. Fortunately, all the IT needs identified by the different offices during the workshop were captured in the developed 2020-2022 ISSP.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 07:38:28', '2019-12-27 10:12:51', '0', '1', ' '),
(64, '1', 24, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'Backup Process', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Some components to secure the server room are not available</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The server room of the Institute is located inside the MIS Section Room and houses the servers of various systems and databases.&nbsp; It contains two rack cabinets, servers, uninterruptible power supply (UPS) apparatus, and other network peripherals. It has three air conditioning units being operated alternately. The following were observed during the audit meeting:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">No fire suppression units were available in case there is a fire incident;</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Air conditioners did not have automatic timers to switch on/off based on the set schedule; and</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Air conditioner systems were installed almost above the rack servers which may result in sparking and fire accident in case there is a water leakage.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 07:40:49', '2019-12-27 14:51:47', '0', '1', ' '),
(65, '1', 25, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'Backup Process', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>ICT Policy Manual of the Institute is not yet being implemented</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">ICT Policies and Procedures ensure that employees use Information and Communications Technology (ICT) facilities and services of the Institute in an appropriate and secure manner.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">MIS Section developed an Information and Communications Technology (ICT) Policy Manual which contains the following policies and standard procedures:</span></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Purchasing of ICT Hardware and Software Policy</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Information Technology Security Policy</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Policy for Getting and Installing Software</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Information Technology Technical Support</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Bring Your Own Device (BYOD) Policy</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">ITDI Website Policy</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Based on the audit interview, these policies are not yet fully implemented. While the MIS Section is already implementing some of the provisions in the above-mentioned policies, it is not yet made official and no monitoring of their implementation is being done.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 07:46:06', '2019-12-27 13:54:59', '0', '1', ' '),
(66, '1', 21, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'Information System Development, Acquisition and Maintenance', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Information systems are not properly documented</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">In order to ensure successful development of an information or application systems, one should &nbsp; follow the System Development Life Cycle (SDLC), a structured and methodical process, which includes planning, analysis, design, implementation, testing and integration, and maintenance.&nbsp; The same structure should also be used for information systems to be developed by a third-party software provider.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Based from 2020-2022 ISSP, the Institutes has a total of 15 information systems being maintained/developed/enhanced.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">MIS Section follows the Waterfall Model during the development of their information systems, which involves gathering of user requirements, creation of interface designs, programming, system testing, deployment and maintenance. However, there were no standard deliverables for every project activity.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">As revealed during the Audit Team&rsquo;s interview, given the number of information system projects being handled by the three staff of MIS Section, they are not able to properly document their information systems. For instance, there was no approved project charter which should contain the goal and objective of the project, scope, its impact, associated risks, timeline of key milestones and project team and stakeholders, among others. Also, it was mentioned that user requirements and design specifications were not fully documented.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 08:02:03', '2019-08-28 08:02:03', '0', '1', ' '),
(67, '1', 26, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'Backup Process', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Some developed information systems already developed are not yet being utilized due to lack of implementation plan</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">ITDI developed various information systems such as R&amp;D Project Monitoring System (RDPMS), Equipment Inventory System, Document Tracking System, Supplies Monitoring System, and Document Tracking System. However, the aforementioned systems are not yet being fully utilized.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">It was mentioned during the Audit Team&rsquo;s interview that MIS Section are required by PMISD Chief to come-up with the following documents for every information system developed to ensure its successful implementation:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Communication Plan</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Risk Management Plan</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">BCP</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Transition Plan</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">During the time of audit, the MIS Section has not prepared the aforementioned documents given the inadequate number of staff.</span></span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 08:21:50', '2019-12-27 13:54:59', '0', '1', ' '),
(68, '1', 18, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'Management of ICT equipment and Network Infrastructure', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>The Institute has not fully implemented its compliance with DPA, its IRR and issuances of the National Privacy Commission (NPC)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Republic Act 10173 or the Data Privacy Act of 2012 is a law that protects and maintains the right of persons to confidentiality by setting a legal list of rules for public and private organizations to regulate the collection, handling, and disposal of all personal information.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Organizations that handle user data is required to assign data protection officer (DPO) as they are legally responsible for keeping their customers&rsquo; data protected from third parties or any form of misuse, internally or externally.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The Institute harmonized their&nbsp; implementation of Data Privacy Act (DPA) with Freedom of Information (FOI) Program by creating a Data Privacy Act Group delegating decision makers, data privacy officers and request receiving officers. Employees are prohibited to give out data to external clients and only the designated officer is allowed to release the documents based on their prepared checklist.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The Management already appointed a DPO-Head and assigned respective DPOs for R&amp;D, Technical, Administrative, and Budget and Finance Services.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Upon validation during the Audit Team&rsquo;s interview, the following activities were not yet being performed:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Perform Privacy Impact Assessments relative to activities, measures, projects, programs, or systems;&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Conduct and cultivate awareness on privacy and data protection within the organization; and</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Create a Privacy Manual</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 08:25:01', '2019-12-27 14:58:54', '0', '1', ' '),
(69, '1', 27, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'Backup Process', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Some components to secure the server room are not available</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The server room of the Institute is located inside the MIS Section room and houses the servers of various systems and databases.&nbsp; It contains two rack cabinets, servers, uninterruptible power supply (UPS) apparatus, and other network peripherals. It has three air conditioning units being operated alternately. The following are observed during the audit meeting:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">No fire suppression units are available in case there is a fire incident;</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Air conditioners do not have automatic timers to switch on/off based on the set schedule; and</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Air conditioner systems are installed almost above the rack servers which may result in sparking and fire accident in case there is a water leakage.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 08:27:22', '2019-12-27 13:54:59', '0', '1', ' '),
(70, '1', 22, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'IT Requirements', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><em>Lack of computer equipment and software to efficiently perform other technology transfer functions</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">It was mentioned during the audit interview that some of the TSD staff have no computers being used.&nbsp; This is also evident in the current ISSP which shows that the Institute has not yet achieved 1:1 employee to computer ratio. Moreover,&nbsp; some of TSD staff are using old computers which are not capable to run product design and video editing software. The software which they are being used for product design (i.e., SOLIDWORKS) is only a 2015 version since they no longer have funds to renew its license.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Furthermore, they hope to have a software for AVPs and technology simulator software which they can use to promote and demonstrate their technologies to their clients more effectively.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 08:32:47', '2019-08-28 08:32:47', '0', '1', ' '),
(72, '1', 23, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'Implementation of Information Systems', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><em>There is a need to enhance the R&amp;D Project Monitoring System (RDPMS)</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">During the time of audit, R&amp;D Project Monitoring System (RDPMS), which they adopted from FNRI, was being enhanced by the MIS Section, to add the following functionalities:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Provide access to PMISD who will monitor the projects;</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Allow project leaders to manage projects even during proposal stage and update technical and financial accomplishments of the projects</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 08:42:55', '2019-08-28 08:42:55', '0', '1', ' '),
(73, '1', 16, '', '3', 'Planning and Management Information Systems', ' ', 'Data Privacy', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>The Institute has not fully implemented its compliance with DPA, its IRR and issuances of the National Privacy Commission (NPC)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Republic Act 10173 or the Data Privacy Act of 2012 is a law that protects and maintains the right of persons to confidentiality by setting a legal list of rules for public and private organizations to regulate the collection, handling, and disposal of all personal information.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Organizations that handle user data is required to assign data protection officer (DPO) as they are legally responsible for keeping their customers&rsquo; data protected from third parties or any form of misuse, internally or externally.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The Institute harmonized their&nbsp; implementation of Data Privacy Act (DPA) with Freedom of Information (FOI) Program by creating a Data Privacy Act Group delegating decision makers, data privacy officers and request receiving officers. Employees are prohibited to give out data to external clients and only the designated officer is allowed to release the documents based on their prepared checklist.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The Management already appointed a DPO-Head and assigned respective DPOs for R&amp;D, Technical, Administrative, and Budget and Finance Services.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Upon validation during the Audit Team&rsquo;s interview, the following activities are not yet being performed:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Perform Privacy Impact Assessments relative to activities, measures, projects, programs, or systems;&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Conduct and cultivate awareness on privacy and data protection within the organization; and</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Create a Privacy Manual</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 08:47:31', '2019-08-28 08:47:31', '0', '1', ' '),
(74, '1', 32, '', '3', 'Technological Services Division', ' ', 'Technology Readiness Assessment', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>Need to institutionalize ITDI&rsquo;s technology readiness assessment tools</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">ITDI performs various modes of&nbsp; technology readiness assessment of its R&amp;D output through the following:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The </span><strong>Technology Audit</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> being conducted with the researchers.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From CY 2016-2018, TSD conducted </span><strong>Technology Readiness Audit</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> with the Industry and DTI for completed projects by evaluating them in terms of maturity level, potential technical or legal issues, advantages over similar technology, IP position, market size, number of adopters, resident expert, among others. Using a scoring system, those with higher scores are to be promoted for technology transfer.</span></span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">They also tried <strong>Market Validation</strong> (Quicklook) of their technology with the prospective customers to get feedback and identify the gaps/grey areas that they also reported to the researchers.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">At the time of the audit, TSD mentioned to the Audit Team that they are still in the process of testing different technology assessment strategies and trying to identify what would fit in with the Institute considering the cost-effectiveness or cost-efficiency of every technology audit process.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There is a great value in institutionalizing the different technology readiness assessment tools being used by the Institute.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 09:42:18', '2019-12-27 15:04:22', '0', '1', ' '),
(75, '1', 33, '', '3', 'Technological Services Division', ' ', 'Technology Readiness Assessment', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><em>Need to involve TSD staff during the early stage of R&amp;D project</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">TSD is expected to start promoting and transferring technology once an R&amp;D project is already completed. However, for a full grasp of the technology to be transferred, they expressed a willingness to be involved even during the early stages of the R&amp;D project. This is to enable them to experience/learn about the technology, identify potential IPs, and define the proper value proposition, especially that most of the R&amp;D outputs are prototypes that need more clinical testing, market testing, and other validation activities. This is a challenge for them since researchers prefer to have their R&amp;D activity audited only at the end of the project.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 10:02:50', '2019-12-27 15:07:10', '0', '1', ' ');
INSERT INTO `form_content` (`id`, `form_001_id`, `auditfinding_no`, `subof`, `author_id`, `audit_area`, `custom_auditarea`, `sub_auditarea`, `auditfinding`, `auditrecommend`, `auditmanageaction`, `action_by`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `archive_status`, `main_area`, `custom_subauditarea`) VALUES
(76, '1', 34, '', '3', 'Technological Services Division', ' ', 'Technology Readiness Assessment', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>Some R&amp;D projects have no identified cooperators</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">During the audit interview, there are projects with no identified prospective cooperators. TSD mentioned that it is desirable if R&amp;D projects already have had identified cooperators so that it would be easier for them to do product/facility/market testing or validation and perform a realistic valuation of technology. For instance, through a cooperator for a ceramic water filter, they were able to identify more realistic spoilage,&nbsp; material, etc.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Some cooperators are willing to co-fund R&amp;D projects especially if they will be provided first &ldquo;crack&rdquo; in its utilization.&nbsp; Identifying and linking with potential cooperators will ensure adoption of research results and responsible use of government resources; hence, it has to be clear who will adopt the R&amp;D output.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 10:04:46', '2019-12-27 15:16:42', '0', '1', ' '),
(77, '1', 35, '', '3', 'Technological Services Division', ' ', 'Technology Readiness Assessment', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>There was a need to increase the number of experts on financial feasibility study/analysis for the developed technologies&nbsp;</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Currently, there are only three staff in TSD who were trained to perform financial feasibility study/analysis for their developed technologies, which involves computation of investment cost, number of years for payback, net present value, time value of money, etc. Accordingly, they explained that it requires a business economics or financial management background&nbsp; to be able to understand and perform the financial analysis.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 10:23:01', '2019-12-27 15:22:19', '0', '1', ' '),
(78, '1', 36, '', '3', 'Technological Services Division', ' ', 'Technology Readiness Assessment', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>There is a need to study why some Technology Transfer Agreements did not prosper&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">It was mentioned during the audit interview that most of the communications sent to the Institute are requests to adopt various ITDI technologies.&nbsp; Upon receiving a request from the interested party, TSD initiates a meeting with the Project Leader to gather technical data and evaluate the client&rsquo;s request.&nbsp; Ideally, TSD meets with the client first to prevent R&amp;D staff from accidentally disclosing confidential information to the client. After assessing the needs of their client, TSD prepares an activity report which is subsequently provided to a concerned R&amp;D unit.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">However, some clients cannot afford the terms and conditions set for technology transfer, including technology fees. Ironically, the FOB&nbsp; sometimes asked them to increase their technology fee.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">There was a time also that after several consultations and revisions of the Technology Commercialization Plan with a client, the technology transfer project did not push through because of other requirements that made the clients no longer interested to continue with the undertaking.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Moreover, there were developed technologies that are dependent on other equipment that the client needs to buy somewhere which becomes a burden to them.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 10:28:02', '2019-12-27 15:25:33', '0', '1', ' '),
(79, '1', 30, '', '4', ' ', 'R&D Divisions', 'Scientific Paper Prepared/Published', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>The number of publication of ITDI in international and ISI journals is too low considering that it is the biggest R&amp;D institute with five (5) R&amp;D Divisions and with diverse industry concerns&nbsp;</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">B<span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">ased on the report submitted by the Planning and Management Information System Division (PMISD), the five (5) R&amp;D Divisions of ITDI prepared/published a total of 78 scientific paper in CY 2012-2018, an average of 11 per year and 2 per R&amp;D Division. </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>(Annex__).</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">There were no targets and accomplishments recorded for CED for CY 2012 and 2017; EBD for CY 2012-2014; FPD for 2012, 2016-2017; MSD for 2012 and 2017 and PTD for 2012-2014 and 2017-2018 as presented in Table 1 and 2 below.&nbsp; During the interview with the R&amp;D Division&rsquo;s staff, from CY 2012-2018, they do not prioritize the preparation of the publication after the completion of the projects. Similarly, per PTD Division Head, they were not able to increase the number of publications, patents, trademarks because they are business-oriented. However, due to the changes in the performance indicators towards the 6Ps, they said that they are trying to catch-up to be able to increase the number of 6Ps of the PTD.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Table 1. No. of Scientific Paper targeted per year 