: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">34</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.1111%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">11</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.1111%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">1</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.1111%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">8</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.1111%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">78</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 10:46:18', '2019-12-26 15:38:10', '0', '1', ' '),
(80, '1', 31, '', '4', ' ', 'R&D Divisions', 'Safekeeping of Project Reports', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>Some of the project documents of the EBD are not kept in a safe location to protect it against damage&nbsp;</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rule 73 of the IRR of R.A. 9470 - National Archives of the Philippines (Storage and Protection of Public Records) states that the Records Officer or any appropriate person responsible for maintaining an office or offices wherein public records are created or kept shall establish such safeguards against damage, removal or loss. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the time of audit and during </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">an interview with the Document Custodian (DC) of the EBD who is tasked to safeguard and keep the documents of the Division, some of the project documents are not available, because according to her, it was damaged by the water leaked from the ceiling of their room. Because of this incident, the said room is not a safe place for the storage of important EBD project documents. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 11:09:22', '2019-12-26 15:42:51', '0', '1', ' '),
(82, '1', 37, '', '3', 'Technological Services Division', ' ', 'Technology Readiness Assessment', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>No policy in place on technology transfer to foreign country</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">ITDI also received various requests from other countries to adopt their technologies.&nbsp; However, as mentioned during the audit interview, it was not clear to them whether they are allowed to transact with a foreign owned company.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Nonetheless, they were able to transfer some technologies (e.g. acetator kit) to other countries.&nbsp; To ensure due diligence when verifying information about the prospective adopter, they course through the communication to the Philippine embassy and corresponding embassy of the requesting country.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 11:16:51', '2019-10-21 09:04:36', '0', '1', ' '),
(83, '1', 38, '', '3', 'Technological Services Division', ' ', 'Technology Packaging and Promotion', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>Marketing tools and promotional materials varied in terms of content</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">TSD serves as the marketing arm of the Institute in terms of promoting the technologies and services of RDIs.&nbsp; Its primary purpose is to conduct technology transfer in various modes. Particularly, the Information and Documentation Section (IDE) is in charge of the promotion and social marketing activities to ensure public awareness of ITDI\'s technologies and establish engagement with the industries.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Because of their externally funded projects, TSD is able to come up with product portfolio including brochures/flyers that provide various information about their technologies. However, their IEC materials (e.g. flyers) varied in terms of content.&nbsp; Some materials contain product description only (e.g. Dual-drum Composter, Cacao Roaster), while others contains additional information such as product capacity (e.g. Water Retort, Freeze Dryer, Spray Dryer), advantages/benefits (e.g. Oil Spill Absorbent Made From Waste), and financial viability (e.g. Nanoclay from local bentonite ore).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Furthermore, Technology Profile (technology brief, marketing plan, business opportunities) and Commercialization Plan for developed technologies also vary in terms of content.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 11:18:46', '2019-10-21 09:06:55', '0', '1', ' '),
(84, '1', 39, '', '3', 'Technological Services Division', ' ', 'Royalties', '<p><strong><em>Royalties are not being received regularly by the Institute</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ITDI provides its researchers with a 40% share of the royalties received from their adoptors in accordance with the conditions set in Administrative Order No. 009, S. 2015. Moreover, as mentioned by TSD to the Audit Team, the 60% share intended for the Institute is reverted back to the Treasury which could have been used by the Institute to support R&amp;D and Technology Transfer activities.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, payment of royalties for every technology/equipment generated by the adoptor is sometimes delayed. Sometimes, the adoptors encountered problems in terms of payments from their clients (e.g. LGUs) which is the reason why their payments for the royalties are delayed. Hence,&nbsp; instead of getting the royalty per equipment sold, the Institute gets the total amount due only when they renew the contract of the adoptor.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 11:21:31', '2019-12-27 15:29:53', '0', '1', ' '),
(85, '1', 40, '', '3', 'Technological Services Division', ' ', 'Intellectual Properties', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><em>IPs and IPRs are not fully protected</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Confidential disclosure of IPs and/or potential IPRs to the head of the funding agency within 30 days from the date of confidential disclosure by the researcher to the Institute is not being observed.</span></span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 11:23:34', '2019-10-21 09:12:19', '0', '1', ' '),
(86, '1', 41, '', '3', 'Technological Services Division', ' ', 'Monitoring and Evaluation', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><em>No documented procedure on the conduct of M&amp;E and impact assessment</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">TSD conducts site visits during construction/fabrication of their technology by the adoptors as a means to monitor and evaluate their technology transfer. A case in point is when their Engineering Services Section checks if the fabricated Bioreactor Intensifier equipment is according to the plans/specs.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">However, after the technology has been transferred, they do not conduct monitoring and evaluation and impact assessment. This has been confirmed by their response during the audit interview and as indicated in the internal control questionnaire (ICQ) of IAS. Moreover, they are unsure if they should be the ones to conduct the M&amp;E considering that they are the ones who facilitate the technology transfer. They think that a separate unit should be responsible for M&amp;E and impact assessment.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-08-28 11:25:00', '2019-10-21 09:16:49', '0', '1', ' '),
(88, '1', 4, '', '38', 'Administrative Management Division', ' ', 'Non-compliance with IRR RA 9184', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Delays&nbsp; in the implementation of infrastructure projects due to the following:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Delay in the Approval and Release of the 2019 Budget</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Limited number of bidders</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Low bid proposals</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Terminated contracts due to poor implementation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-10-25 07:11:22', '2019-10-25 07:11:22', '0', '2', ' '),
(89, '1', 28, '', '4', 'Office of the Director', ' ', ' ', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>T<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">he&nbsp; </span></em></strong><strong><em>R&amp;D Roadmaps&nbsp; of the R&amp;D Divisions need to be fully developed</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The R&amp;D Roadmap is a tool used to set the R&amp;D direction of an organization as well as in developing its technological capabilities. The said roadmaps should be the basis for planning and implementing R&amp;D programs/projects of the division. It must be &ldquo;living&rdquo; documents that are monitored and updated regularly to reflect new data, technology advances, and changing business conditions.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The five (5) R&amp;D roadmaps </span><strong>(Annex D)</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> of the R&amp;D Divisions namely Chemicals and Energy Division (CED), Environment and Biotechnology Division (EBD), Food Processing Division (FPD), Material Science Division (MSD) and Packaging Technology Division (PTD) were presented to the Audit Team. However, the following were noted in the CED, EBD and FPD roadmaps:</span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The roadmaps look more like a listing of the different R&amp;D projects being implemented by each division.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">There were no separate roadmaps for Environment and Biotechnology for the EBD and Chemicals and Energy for the CED.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The roadmap is more of an S&amp;T investment portfolio rather than an S&amp;T direction for technology or R&amp;D.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The incremental innovations are not identified that can add up to new technologies and products in the future.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The roadmap did not highlight the opportunities for breakthrough innovations to accelerate the R&amp;D process and continuous engagement with various stakeholders.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-10-30 15:27:18', '2019-12-26 15:15:56', '0', '1', ' '),
(90, '1', 3, '', '2', ' ', 'Management and Planning', 'ITDI\'s Broad Mandate vs Low Budget', '<p><strong>Need to revisit ITDI\'s mandate, areas of coverage and the organizational structure in the light of the upcoming Rightsizing Program of the government</strong></p>\r\n<p>ITDI as the biggest RDI covers a wide area from which to conduct applied R&amp;D and develop technologies and innovations for transfer to its end-users. Initially per EO 128 (1987) these areas included chemicals, minerals, food processing, fuels, energy, materials science, microbiology, genetics, wlwctronics, and process control. During ITDI\'s Rationalization Program in 2010, some of these areas were consolidated to the following: environment, biotechnology, chemicals, energy, with&nbsp; the introduction of packaging technology and retention of food processing and materials science. Considering the limited R&amp;D budget, however, and looking at the list of R&amp;D projects funded, not all of these areas mentioned were provided with sufficient R&amp;D funds to be able to generate relevant and significant products/technologies/ services to the industries.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Moreover, it is also ITDI\'s mandate to link with other government agencies in its conduct of technology transfer activities. There were no visible dynamic linkages developed with government agencies as a mechanism to drive technology transfer. ITDI directly introduced to the end-users technologies developed in industries or the requesting local government unit.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A broad mandate coupled with low budget provided for R&amp;D and Technology Transfer have affected ITDI&rsquo;s dynamism and relevance to the industries/stakeholders it serves.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-11-05 09:50:41', '2019-12-12 18:21:52', '0', '1', ' '),
(91, '1', 42, '', '4', ' ', 'R&D Divisions', 'Monitoring and Evaluation', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><em>No regular monitoring and evaluation (M&amp;E) conducted for the Energy Audit activities of the Chemicals and Energy Division (CED)</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The CED\'s energy systems optimization or the energy audit is defined as a critical examination of an energy-consuming facility and a starting point for implementation and control of energy efficiency and conservation program for MSMEs. From CY 2012-2018, CED has conducted a total of 142 energy audits to various MSMEs and public institutions/organizations and recorded a total potential savings of Php16M. Of the 273 energy audit activities </span><strong><em>(Annex G)</em></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> of the CED from CY 1999-2018, only six (6) industries were monitored by the CED and the DOST Regional Office (RO) No. III.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The CED has also recorded a total of Php734,000 actual energy savings per year for the three (3) MSMEs namely; Global Food Solutions Inc., Honda Cars Makati, Inc., and Allied Metals Inc. during their monitoring activity in 2017. Moreover, the DOST RO No. III has identified the total additional potential savings of Php785,000 for the three (3) industries they monitored in 2015 namely; Wiggies Ice, Angel Famous Gourmet Food and Asia Ceramics. However, it was noted that the M&amp;E of the energy audit conducted is not a regular activity of the CED.&nbsp; Also, per interview with the OIC, Chief of the CED, they do not conduct monitoring and evaluation and impact assessment due to lack of funds of the division.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-11-06 17:06:06', '2019-12-26 15:45:29', '0', '1', ' '),
(92, '1', 8, '', '2', ' ', 'Management and Planning', 'Vision-Mission Statement', '<p><strong>ITDI&rsquo;s vision-mission statements are broad and need to be clear-cut and strategic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The wide vision of becoming a recognized industry partner for STI and a common mission to contribute in making local industries globally competitive&nbsp; resulted in broad strategies and programs for ITDI. For instance, the strategic objectives include: to </span>establish state-of-the-art STI facilities, establish centers of excellence in STI, increase STI services, and increase local and international collaboration/linkages.&nbsp; The program thrusts, on the other hand, under the various divisions are likewise broad in scope: (1) Environment and Biotechnology Division-biofuels, bioremediation, enzyme technology, industrial fermentation, and waste treatment technologies; (2) Materials Science Division- nanotechnology, surface science engineering, polymers/plastics R&amp;D, ceramics R&amp;D, composites R&amp;D; (3) Chemicals &amp; Energy Division - renewable energy, pharmaceuticals, industrial chemicals, process development; (4) Food Processing - food Engineering, food safety standards, &amp; processed foods; (5) Packaging Technology Division- Packaging development, label design for food/non food products, packaging testing, transport packaging design &amp; performance evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>To be able to propel development for the country by providing relevant technologies and services to the industry, the goals and objectives of ITDI n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">eed to be clear-cut, paved in roadmaps, and focused on an agreed direction that it will commit to pursue in the next 5-10 years, with strong partnership with the industry, goverment agecies, and the local government under the leadership of the DOST. It was noted that the strategic objectives are supply driven, more than demand driven. There was no document shown that there was meeting of minds among stakeholders/target industries on what ITDI state-of-the-art facilities/equipment, STI centers of excellence and services they need to be able to play competitively in the bigger or even global arena.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ITDI has yet to put all of these considerations in a Strategic Plan that will be its guide in redirecting the Institute from functional to strategic.</span></p>', '', ' ', ' ', ' ', '2019-12-12 18:26:27', '2019-12-26 15:58:47', '0', '1', ' '),
(93, '1', 8, '', '2', ' ', 'Management and Planning', 'ITDI\'s Support to DOST Programs', '<p><strong>ITDI&rsquo;s vision-mission statements are broad and need to be clear-cut and strategic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The wide vision of becoming a recognized industry partner for STI and a common mission to contribute in making local industries globally competitive&nbsp; resulted in broad strategies and programs for ITDI. For instance, the strategic objectives include: to </span>establish state-of-the-art STI facilities, establish centers of excellence in STI, increase STI services, and increase local and international collaboration/linkages.&nbsp; The program thrusts, on the other hand, under the various divisions are likewise broad in scope: (1) Environment and Biotechnology Division-biofuels, bioremediation, enzyme technology, industrial fermentation, and waste treatment technologies; (2) Materials Science Division- nanotechnology, surface science engineering, polymers/plastics R&amp;D, ceramics R&amp;D, composites R&amp;D; (3) Chemicals &amp; Energy Division - renewable energy, pharmaceuticals, industrial chemicals, process development; (4) Food Processing - food Engineering, food safety standards, &amp; processed foods; (5) Packaging Technology Division- Packaging development, label design for food/non food products, packaging testing, transport packaging design &amp; performance evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>To be able to propel development for the country by providing relevant technologies and services to the industry, the goals and objectives of ITDI n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">eed to be clear-cut, paved in roadmaps, and focused on an agreed direction that it will commit to pursue in the next 5-10 years, with strong partnership with the industry, goverment agecies, and the local government under the leadership of the DOST.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ITDI has yet to put all of these considerations in a Stra